{"id":"1807.06452","submitter":"Evgeny Khukhro","authors":"E. I. Khukhro and P. Shumyatsky","title":"Compact groups all elements of which are almost right Engel","comments":"arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:1610.02079,\n  arXiv:1512.06097","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We say that an element $g$ of a group $G$ is almost right Engel if there is a\nfinite set ${\\mathscr R}(g)$ such that for every $x\\in G$ all sufficiently long\ncommutators $[...[[g,x],x],\\dots ,x]$ belong to ${\\mathscr R}(g)$, that is, for\nevery $x\\in G$ there is a positive integer $n(x,g)$ such that\n$[...[[g,x],x],\\dots ,x]\\in {\\mathscr R}(g)$ if $x$ is repeated at least\n$n(x,g)$ times. Thus, $g$ is a right Engel element precisely when we can choose\n${\\mathscr R}(g)=\\{ 1\\}$.\n  We prove that if all elements of a compact (Hausdorff) group $G$ are almost\nright Engel, then $G$ has a finite normal subgroup $N$ such that $G/N$ is\nlocally nilpotent. If in addition there is a uniform bound $|{\\mathscr\nR}(g)|\\leq m$ for the orders of the corresponding sets, then the subgroup $N$\ncan be chosen of order bounded in terms of $m$. The proofs use the\nWilson--Zelmanov theorem saying that Engel profinite groups are locally\nnilpotent and previous results of the authors about compact groups all elements\nof which are almost left Engel.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 14 Jul 2018 13:21:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-18"}
